# ⚙️ Day 4 – Hands-On Tasks

## 🔹 Task 1 – Script Execution Permissions

### Objective
Learn how to make scripts executable and run them securely in Linux.

### Commands Used
```bash
# Create script
vim deploy.sh

# Add script content
echo "echo Deployment Started" > deploy.sh

# Check permissions
ls -l deploy.sh

# Give execute permission
chmod +x deploy.sh

# Run script
./deploy.sh
```

### Learning Outcome
- Understanding execute permissions
- Running shell scripts securely
- Basic Linux permission management

---

## 🔹 Task 2 – File Permission Correction

### Objective
Fix incorrect file permissions using chmod.

### Commands Used
```bash
# Create sample file
touch secure.txt

# Remove all permissions
chmod 000 secure.txt

# Verify permissions
ls -l secure.txt

# Correct permissions
chmod 644 secure.txt

# Verify updated permissions
ls -l secure.txt
```

### Learning Outcome
- Identifying permission issues
- Restoring proper file access
- Understanding secure permission practices

---

## 🔹 Task 3 – String Replacement

### Objective
Replace text inside files using sed.

### Commands Used
```bash
# Create sample config file
echo "Environment=dev" > config.txt

# View file content
cat config.txt

# Replace string
sed -i 's/dev/prod/g' config.txt

# Verify changes
cat config.txt
```

### Learning Outcome
- Automating text replacement
- Updating configuration values efficiently
- Using sed for DevOps automation tasks

